`/`SessionEnd`. Interactive tmux-based tests get the full lifecycle.\\n     8→\\n     9→## Static Checks\\n    10→\\n    11→| Check | Result | Notes |\\n    12→|-------|--------|-------|\\n    13→| Binary present | PASS | `/Users/robin/.local/bin/agent` |\\n    14→| Help available | PASS | Full CLI help with subcommands |\\n    15→| Version info | PASS | `2026.02.13-41ac335` |\\n    16→| Hook keywords | PASS | `session`, `resume`, `continue` in help |\\n    17→| Session keywords | PASS | `--resume`, `--continue`, `ls` (list sessions) |\\n    18→| Config directory | PASS | `~/.cursor/`, `.cursor/` (project-local) |\\n    19→| Documentation | PASS | https://cursor.com/docs/agent/hooks, https://cursor.com/docs/cli/using |\\n    20→\\n    21→## Binary\\n    22→\\n    23→- Name: `agent`\\n    24→- Version: `2026.02.13-41ac335`\\n    25→- Install: `curl -fsSL https://cursor.com/install-agent | bash` (or via Cursor IDE: install shell integration)\\n    26→- Also accessible as: `cursor agent` (when Cursor IDE is installed)\\n    27→\\n    28→## Hook Mechanism\\n    29→\\n    30→- Config file: `.cursor/hooks.json` (project-local) or `~/.cursor/hooks.json` (user-global)\\n    31→- Config format: JSON\\n    32→- Hook registration: Array of `{\\\"command\\\": \\\"...\\\", \\\"matcher\\\": \\\"...\\\"}` entries per hook type (matcher is optional, used for tool-use hooks)\\n    33→\\n    34→### Hook Names and When They Fire\\n    35→\\n    36→| Native Hook Name | When It Fires | Entire EventType | Fires in `-p` mode? |\\n    37→|-----------------|---------------|-----------------|---------------------|\\n    38→| `sessionStart` | New conversation created | `SessionStart` | Yes |\\n    39→| `beforeSubmitPrompt` | After user presses send, before backend request | `TurnStart` | **No** |\\n    40→| `stop` | Agent loop ends (one turn completes) | `TurnEnd` | **No** |\\n    41→| `sessionEnd` | Conversation ends | `SessionEnd` | Yes |\\n    42→| `preCompact` | Before context compaction | `Compaction` | Needs long context |\\n    43→| `subagentStart` | Before spawning a subagent (Task tool) | `SubagentStart` | Yes (when subagent used) |\\n    44→| `subagentStop` | Subagent completes | `SubagentEnd` | Yes (when subagent used) |\\n    45→| `preToolUse` | Before any tool execution | *(not mapped — informational)* | Yes |\\n    46→| `postToolUse` | After tool execution | *(not mapped — informational)* | Yes |\\n    47→\\n    48→### Hook Input (stdin JSON)\\n    49→\\n    50→All hooks share these common fields:\\n    51→\\n    52→```json\\n    53→{\\n    54→  \\\"conversation_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\",\\n    55→  \\\"generation_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\",\\n    56→  \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.2-codex-xhigh-fast\\\",\\n    57→  \\\"hook_event_name\\\": \\\"sessionStart\\\",\\n    58→  \\\"cursor_version\\\": \\\"2026.02.13-41ac335\\\",\\n    59→  \\\"workspace_roots\\\": [\\\"/path/to/repo\\\"],\\n    60→  \\\"user_email\\\": \\\"user@example.com\\\",\\n    61→  \\\"transcript_path\\\": null\\n    62→}\\n    63→```\\n    64→\\n    65→**Important:** `transcript_path` is **always `null`** in CLI mode. The existing cursor agent handles this via `resolveTranscriptRef()` which computes the path dynamically from the repo root.\\n    66→\\n    67→#### sessionStart additional fields\\n    68→\\n    69→```json\\n    70→{\\n    71→  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\",\\n    72→  \\\"is_background_agent\\\": false\\n    73→}\\n    74→```\\n    75→\\n    76→Note: IDE also sends `composer_mode: \\\"agent\\\"` — CLI omits this field.\\n    77→\\n    78→#### sessionEnd additional fields\\n    79→\\n    80→```json\\n    81→{\\n    82→  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\",\\n    83→  \\\"reason\\\": \\\"completed\\\",\\n    84→  \\\"duration_ms\\\": 5505,\\n    85→  \\\"is_background_agent\\\": false,\\n    86→  \\\"final_status\\\": \\\"completed\\\"\\n    87→}\\n    88→```\\n    89→\\n    90→#### beforeSubmitPrompt additional fields (interactive mode only)\\n    91→\\n    92→```json\\n    93→{\\n    94→  \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"user prompt text\\\"\\n    95→}\\n    96→```\\n    97→\\n    98→#### stop additional fields (interactive mode only)\\n    99→\\n   100→```json\\n   101→{\\n   102→  \\\"status\\\": \\\"completed\\\",\\n   103→  \\\"loop_count\\\": 0\\n   104→}\\n   105→```\\n   106→\\n   107→#### subagentStart additional fields\\n   108→\\n   109→```json\\n   110→{\\n   111→  \\\"subagent_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\",\\n   112→  \\\"subagent_type\\\": \\\"generalPurpose\\\",\\n   113→  \\\"subagent_model\\\": \\\"model-name\\\",\\n   114→  \\\"task\\\": \\\"task description\\\",\\n   115→  \\\"parent_conversation_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\",\\n   116→  \\\"tool_call_id\\\": \\\"id\\\",\\n   117→  \\\"is_parallel_worker\\\": false\\n   118→}\\n   119→```\\n   120→\\n   121→#### subagentStop additional fields\\n   122→\\n   123→```json\\n   124→{\\n   125→  \\\"subagent_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\",\\n   126→  \\\"subagent_type\\\": \\\"generalPurpose\\\",\\n   127→  \\\"status\\\": \\\"completed\\\",\\n   128→  \\\"duration_ms\\\": 5000,\\n   129→  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"result text\\\",\\n   130→  \\\"parent_conversation_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\",\\n   131→  \\\"message_count\\\": 10,\\n   132→  \\\"tool_call_count\\\": 3,\\n   133→  \\\"modified_files\\\": [\\\"file.txt\\\"],\\n   134→  \\\"loop_count\\\": 1,\\n   135→  \\\"task\\\": \\\"task description\\\",\\n   136→  \\\"description\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n   137→  \\\"agent_transcript_path\\\": \\\"/path/to/transcript\\\"\\n   138→}\\n   139→```\\n   140→\\n   141→#### preToolUse additional fields\\n   142→\\n   143→```json\\n   144→{\\n   145→  \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"Write\\\",\\n   146→  \\\"tool_input\\\": {\\\"file_path\\\": \\\"/path\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"...\\\"},\\n   147→  \\\"tool_use_id\\\": \\\"call_xxx\\\\nctc_xxx\\\"\\n   148→}\\n   149→```\\n   150→\\n   151→#### postToolUse additional fields\\n   152→\\n   153→```json\\n   154→{\\n   155→  \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"Write\\\",\\n   156→  \\\"tool_input\\\": 