cted — this is cursor-cli-specific test infra\\n\\n### Proposed fix\\n\\n**File:** `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go` — `startInteractiveSession()` or `Bootstrap()`\\n\\n**Change:** Pre-create the cursor config directory before launching the agent to prevent the ENOENT race:\\n```go\\n// In Bootstrap() or startInteractiveSession(), ensure ~/.config/cursor/ exists\\nconfigDir := filepath.Join(os.Getenv(\\\"HOME\\\"), \\\".config\\\", \\\"cursor\\\")\\nos.MkdirAll(configDir, 0o755)\\n```\\n\\nThis is the same pattern used for other agents (e.g., opencode gets a pre-written config in `repo.go:93-100`).\\n\\n**Alternative:** Add `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` or cursor-specific config env var to the tmux env forwarding list, pointing to a per-test temp directory for isolation.\\n\\n## No re-runs needed\\n\\nSince the user provided an artifact path (not test names), and this is a clear test-infra issue visible from artifacts alone, no re-runs are needed. The classification is unambiguous from the error output.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\nAfter applying the fix:\\n```bash\\nmise run test:e2e:canary        # Must pass\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint    # Code quality\\n```\\n\\nOptional (costs tokens): `mise run test:e2e --agent cursor-cli TestResumeSquashMergeMultipleCheckpoints`\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":990,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":80602,\"output_tokens\":38,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":990,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnczMD6L6nkosmDLBsZY\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"0d429457-8698-408a-ae35-83e1ed80ff8b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T22:32:55.339Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"0d429457-8698-408a-ae35-83e1ed80ff8b\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\